    "recap_headline": "United States Air Force Academy",
    "recap_text": "RENO, Nev., -\nAir Force (7-12, 3-1) fought but came up short to Nevada (13-6, 4-0), 10-7, in game one of the series on Friday evening at Don Weir Field. The Falcons totaled 12 hits while the pitchers combined for six strikeouts.\nOffensively,\nT.J. Oster\nled the Falcons with a perfect 3-for-3 night and two RBIs.\nBen Niednagel\n,\nWalker Zapp\n,\nLuke Elmore\n, and\nLandon Boyd\naccounted for one RBI apiece.\nJosh Holst\nthrew 4.2 innings in his start, striking out four batters and allowing five runs.\nGunner Gilmore\n(0-1) recorded one strikeout and four runs allowed in 0.2 innings. Following a scoreless 0.2 innings from\nJoey Collier\n,\nEaston Miller\nand\nDavis Rhyne\nboth logged an inning.\nThe Falcons were first on the board, 2-0 in the top of the third. Oster led off with a single and advanced on a sacrifice bunt from\nBrooks Burdine\n. A\nKayden Bradshaw\nsingle put runners on the corners, allowing Oster to score on an error by Nevada's pitcher. Zapp recorded an RBI single to close the frame.\nNevada answered with a solo home run to trim the deficit in the bottom of three, 2-1.\nIn the top of the fourth, Air Force responded with another pair of runs to lead 4-1. With one away, Elmore was hit by a pitch and sent across the plate on a first-pitch double from Boyd. An RBI double from Oster scored another run.\nThe Wolf Pack pulled ahead, 5-4, in the bottom of five.\nThe Birds kept up their offensive momentum to shift back in front, 6-5, in the top of the sixth. After\nWyatt Hanoian\ndrew a walk to start the inning,\nTripp Garrish\ndoubled to put runners on the corners. Elmore grounded out to send a run home while Oster followed with his third hit of the day to plate Garrish.\nIn the bottom of six, Nevada reclaimed their lead at 9-6.\nAir Force tacked on their final run of the evening at 9-7 in the top of the stretch after Burdine singled, stole second, and scored on an RBI single from Niednagel.\nThe bottom of the eighth saw the Wolf Pack solidify the score at 10-7.\nThe two teams will meet for game two on Saturday March 21 at 2 p.m. PT/3 p.m. MT.",
